When Christian apologists explain with extreme assurance they know what they're talking about, it's often a smokescreen. 

This video is a look at Christian Apologist Mike Winger's claims about things he's absolutely sure about (like who's a fake Christian in his view) and things he doesn't know or want to answer in public.

Why the ignorance on some things while claiming extreme confidence on other things? Doesn't the Bible and the Holy Spirit show you all answers? 

If not, why? 

If yes, why do Christians disagree on nearly every single doctrine? 

Is Mike Winger's God different than the Catholic God? The Calvinist God? The Mormon God? Why? And how does he know? 

